CBRE is pleased to present 1/188 Plenty Road, Preston, for lease and available now.

Located only 11kms* north of the Melbourne CBD, this historically tightly held asset offers nothing but potential.
The proximity to public transport including bus, tram and train services only add to this already fantastic offering.

•	Warehouse Area: 1,530sqm
•	39 on-site car spaces approx.*
•	Multiple container height roller doors
•	Tram stop in front of building
•	Three (3) phase power
•	Dual street frontages plus rear way access
•	Zoned Commercial 1
•	Close to CBD

For further details on this property or your commercial property needs, please contact the marketing agents from CBRE.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE Large Format Retail is pleased to present as the exclusive agents a rare opportunity for lease in the heart of the Preston Large Format Retail precinct.

The tenancy is positioned fantastically along Bell Street enjoying dominant exposure to 41,000* passing cars daily. The Bell Street strip is home to a plethora of Large Format Retailers including Harvey Norman, Officeworks, Rays Outdoors, Nick Scali, Baby Bunting, Petbarn, Adairs, JB HiFi, Beacon Lighting, Super Amart & many more.

Preston is a suburb in Melbourne, Victoria, Australia, located 9 km north from Melbourne’s central business district. Its Local Government Area is the City of Darebin.

The subject property is strategically located adjacent to Repco, immediately adjacent to the corner of Bell Street and Chifley Drive, a busy and strategic intersection. Also in immediate proximity is the Northland Regional Shopping Centre, the largest predominantly single-level shopping centre in Melbourne. It has more than 330 stores all spread on one floor but cinemas, Playtime and Pancake Parlour is on the top level.

The Northland Shopping precinct represents the hub of the Prestons shopping, According to The Darebin 2007 Household Survey 37.4% of Larger Household Goods shopping was enjoyed at the Northland Homemaker Centre.
